"GRNsight is an open source web application and service for visualizing models of small-scale gene regulatory networks (GRNs) and protein-protein interaction networks (PPIs). GRNsight is a joint project of the Loyola Marymount University Bioinformatics and Biomathematics Groups"

"Most users will want to access GRNsight through the web application at http://dondi.github.io/GRNsight/. The source code is available for developers who wish to run their own instance of the GRNsight web service and/or web client."
